# User Research Skill

Generate professional user research documents as self-contained HTML.

## Full Documentation

Read complete skill details from: `docs/skills/user-research-design.md`
Read theme CSS from: `docs/DESIGN-SYSTEM.md`

## Supported Frameworks

### 1. User Personas
- Name, photo placeholder, quote
- Demographics (age, location, role)
- Goals & Motivations
- Pain Points & Frustrations
- Behaviors & Habits
- Tech Savviness
- Preferred Channels

### 2. Customer Journey Map
- Stages/Phases (Awareness → Purchase → Retention)
- Actions per stage
- Thoughts (what they're thinking)
- Emotions (positive/neutral/negative)
- Touchpoints (where interaction happens)
- Pain Points (frustrations)
- Opportunities (improvements)

### 3. Jobs to be Done (JTBD)
- Job Statement: "When [situation], I want to [motivation], so I can [outcome]"
- Functional Jobs (practical tasks)
- Emotional Jobs (feelings sought)
- Social Jobs (how they want to be perceived)
- Hiring Criteria (why they'd choose your solution)

### 4. Empathy Map
- **Says** - Direct quotes
- **Thinks** - Internal thoughts
- **Does** - Observable actions
- **Feels** - Emotional state
- **Pains** - Frustrations, fears
- **Gains** - Wants, needs, success measures

## Key Components

- **Persona cards** - Avatar, demographics, goals, pain points
- **Journey grid** - Stage columns × aspect rows
- **JTBD cards** - Statement + functional/emotional/social
- **Empathy quadrants** - 2x2 + pains/gains

